gmfModemTable.name: gmfModemTable
gmfModemTable.description: This table contains information about all GM-F converters in all racks.

mdmRack.name: mdmRack
mdmRack.description: The index of the rack where the converter is installed.

mdmModem.name: mdmModem
mdmModem.description: This entry displays the slot number where the corresponding converter is installed in the rack.

mdmPosition.name: mdmPosition
mdmPosition.description: This entry displays the location of the corresponding converter: 'local' or 'remote'. The converter which is plugged into a managed rack is 'local', the counterpart is 'remote'.

mdmModemName.name: mdmModemName
mdmModemName.description: The verbal name of this converter.

mdmInterfaceEmulationMode.name: mdmInterfaceEmulationMode
mdmInterfaceEmulationMode.description: Interface mode of the unit: 'dte', 'dce', 'te' or 'nt'.

mdmModemProperty.name: mdmModemProperty
mdmModemProperty.description: This entry displays the speed class of the GM-F: 'e1' or 't1'.

mdmLineEmulationMode.name: mdmLineEmulationMode
mdmLineEmulationMode.description: Line mode of the unit: 'te' or 'nt'.

mdmClockSystem.name: mdmClockSystem
mdmClockSystem.description: The clock system of the link: 'dual' or 'single'.

mdmClockSource.name: mdmClockSource
mdmClockSource.description: The clock source of the link: 'internal', 'external', or 'remote'.

mdmDataRate.name: mdmDataRate
mdmDataRate.description: The data rate at the interface in bits per seconds. The data rate at the remote counterpart changes simultaneously. A data rate of 2.048 Mbps (E1) automatically disables CRC4, sets mdmStartTimeslot to 'unframed', enables time slot 16, and disables remote access. A data rate of 1.984 Mbps (E1) automatically sets mdmStartTimeslot to 'timeslot-1', enables time slot 16 and sets mdmRemoteAccessMode to 'via timeslot 0 sa4-bit'. A data rate of 1.544 Mbps (T1) automatically sets mdmStartTimeslot to 'unframed' and disables remote access.

mdmStartTimeslot.name: mdmStartTimeslot
mdmStartTimeslot.description: This entry determines the start time slot for framing. Start time slot and data rate must match. A start time slot which is too high will be ignored. The remote unit's configuration changes simultaneously.

mdmTimeslotSize.name: mdmTimeslotSize
mdmTimeslotSize.description: This entry determines the size of the time slots: 'nx64k' or 'nx56k'. 'nx56k' is valid for T1 units only. The remote unit's configuration changes simultaneously.

mdmTimeslot16.name: mdmTimeslot16
mdmTimeslot16.description: This entry enables or disables time slot 16. If it is disabled, it will not be used for data transmission but for framing. Valid for E1 units only.

mdmCRC4Generation.name: mdmCRC4Generation
mdmCRC4Generation.description: This entry enables or disables the generation of a CRC4 check sum. Valid for E1 units only.

mdmFramingMode.name: mdmFramingMode
mdmFramingMode.description: The T1 framing mode: 'd4' or 'esf'. The remote unit's configuration changes simultaneously. Valid for T1 units only.

mdmCodingMode.name: mdmCodingMode
mdmCodingMode.description: The T1 coding mode: 'ami' or 'b8zs'. The remote unit's configuration changes simultaneously. Valid for T1 units only.

mdmScrambler.name: mdmScrambler
mdmScrambler.description: This entry enables or disables scrambling.

mdmRemoteAccessMode.name: mdmRemoteAccessMode
mdmRemoteAccessMode.description: The remote access mode: 'disable', 'via-next-free-timeslot', 'via-timeslot-0-Sa4-bit', or 'via-unframed-line'. The value 'via-next-free-timeslot' means that one time slot higher than the last data time slot is used for remote access. The value 'via-timeslot-0-Sa4-bit' means that the sa4-bit in time slot 0 is used for remote access (for E1 units only). The value 'via-unframed-line' is valied for data rates of 2048 Kbps (E1) or 1544 Kbps (T1) only. With a data rate of 1536 Kbps (T1). remote management is not available. The remote unit's configuration changes simultaneously.

mdmForcedRemoteAccess.name: mdmForcedRemoteAccess
mdmForcedRemoteAccess.description: Valid if 'mdmRemoteAccessMode' is set to 'via-unframed-line'. Activation of remote management: 'on' or 'off'. Status 'on' enables management of remote unit. During this process the link is restricted to management data. The transmission of user data is interrupted. Status 'off' disables management of remote unit. The link transmits user data.

mdmTDPhaseLocking.name: mdmTDPhaseLocking
mdmTDPhaseLocking.description: This entry defines the data phase locking for I/F data: 'positive-clock-slope' or 'negative-clock-slope'.

mdmLineBuiltOut.name: mdmLineBuiltOut
mdmLineBuiltOut.description: The T1 transmission mode of the unit. Valid for T1 units only.

mdmCRC6Test.name: mdmCRC6Test
mdmCRC6Test.description: This entry enables the execution of a CRC6 test. Write requests with values other than 'start' or 'stop' will be rejected. Valid for T1 units only.

mdmCRC6Status.name: mdmCRC6Status
mdmCRC6Status.description: This entry indicates the status of the CRC6 test. Valid for T1 units only.

mdmCRC6Error.name: mdmCRC6Error
mdmCRC6Error.description: This entry indicates the number of errors detected during the last 60 seconds.
